.TH "fsl_chan_set_dst_loop_size" 9 "fsl_chan_set_dst_loop_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_chan_set_dst_loop_size \- Set destination address hold transfer size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fsl_chan_set_dst_loop_size
.BI "(struct fsldma_chan *chan "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chan" 12
Freescale DMA channel
.IP "size" 12
Address loop size, 0 for disable loop
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The set destination address hold transfer size. The destination
address hold or loop transfer size is when the DMA transfer
data to destination address (TA), if the loop size is 4, the DMA will
write data to TA, TA + 1, TA + 2, TA + 3, then loop back to TA,
TA + 1 ... and so on.
